    • Method Detail

      • waitUntilAdded

        public State waitUntilAdded(long t,
                            java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit timeUnit)
        Block until the Job has been added or the add has failed. Subject to timeout.
        Parameters:
        t - Max time to wait
        timeUnit - Units for t
        Returns:
        The state of the job after adding. Typically WAIT or READY but may be a terminal state if the add failed, was canceled, succeeded early, or was assimilated by another job. In the event of a timeout, the job's current state is returned.

      • waitForTerminalState

        public State waitForTerminalState(long t,
                                  java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit timeUnit)
        Block until the job has reached a terminal State (see State.isTerminal()). Subject to timeout.
        Parameters:
        t - Max time to wait
        timeUnit - Units for t
        Returns:
        The final state of the job. In the event of a timeout, the job's current state is returned.
